        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "describing",
          "value": "Mathlib's ODE files give only local existence (`IsPicardLindelof.exists_eq_forall_mem_Icc_hasDerivWithinAt`); no theorem stating that a global Lipschitz bound yields a solution on all of ℝ was found.",
          "format": "text/plain"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Picard%E2%80%93Lindel%C3%B6f_theorem?oldid=1346301030",
        "selector": {
          "type": "TextQuoteSelector",
          "exact": "if {{math|&thinsp;''f''&thinsp;}} is globally Lipschitz"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "urn:wikilean:Picard-Lindelof_theorem:anno-15",
      "type": "Annotation",
      "motivation": "classifying",
      "created": "2026-05-27T18:35:34+00:00",
      "generator": {
        "type": "Software",
        "name": "WikiLean 2-agent annotation pipeline",
        "homepage": "https://github.com/Deicyde/WikiLean"
      },
      "body": [
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "classifying",
          "value": "not_formalized"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "tagging",
          "value": "example"
        },
        {
          "type": "TextualBody",
          "purpose": "describing",
          "value": "Shows that local Lipschitz (or even smoothness) is not enough for global existence: the IVP dy/dt = y², y(0)=1 has solution y(t)=1/(1−t), undefined at t=1. Mathlib has the local existence theorems but no formalisation of this specific blow-up counter-example.",
          "format": "text/plain"
        }
      ],
      "target": {
        "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Picard%E2%80%93Lindel%C3%B6f_theorem?oldid=1346301030",
        "selector": {
          "type": "TextQuoteSelector",
          "exact": "If f is only locally Lipschitz"
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "urn:wikilean:Picard-Lindelof_theorem:anno-16",
      "type": "Annotation",
